    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.8.0-dev commit 9e442c17eeffca934c1de3674b910458e04c989b\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nyes, vim 8.1.3741. Vim has the same behavior when `laststatus` is 2.\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nUbuntu 20.04 focal(on the Windows Subsystem for Linux)\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nxterm 3.1\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n1. Create file `~/init.vim`\r\n2. Write into `~/init.vim` (this is the minimal config that can reproduce the issue, notice that `cursorline` has to be set):\r\n\r\n```vimscript\r\nset incsearch\r\nset cursorline\r\nfunc RedrawStatus(timer)\r\n  execute \"redrawstatus\"\r\nendfunc\r\nlet timer = timer_start(1000, 'RedrawStatus', { 'repeat': -1 })\r\n```\r\n3. Open nvim using `nvim -u ~/init.vim`\r\n4. In nvim open an arbitraty file, use `/` to search for a word\r\n5. You can observe that IncSearch highlight disappears when `:redrawstatus` is fired by the timer\r\n6. Vim have the same problem. You can verify it by using the same config file and **set `laststatus` to 2 explicitly**.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nIncSearch highlighting should not disappear when `:redrawstatus` is fired.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nIncSearch highlighting disappears when `:redrawstatus` is fired.\r\nHere is the demonstration of this issue:\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76579810/172341787-5ba03472-05f0-4c36-ad01-a043c6f0c75f.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
